	<p pid="a.17.5/1">asked Her Majesty's Government:</p>
	<p pid="a.17.5/2" qnum="HL1306">Further to the Written Answer by Lord Whitty on 7 February (<i>WA 90</i>), why the Independent Scientific Group has refused to disclose the results of post mortems on badgers; whether the results are known to the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs; and whether the results should be in the public domain.</p>
</ques>
