	<p pid="a.17.8/1">asked Her Majesty's Government:</p>
	<p pid="a.17.8/2" qnum="HL1133">How many badger carcasses were examined by the Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food between (a) 1974 and 1995; (b) 1996 and 1998; and (c) 1998 and 2004 in the United Kingdom; how many were found to be positive for <i>mycobacterium bovis</i>; and what are the numbers in each case for England and Wales, and for each county within England and Wales.</p>
</ques>
